WEBVTT

01:36.040 --> 01:37.720
ADAPTED FROM THE NOVEL OF THE SAME NAME
BY ZHU YI ON WWW.JJWXC.NET

01:37.800 --> 01:41.000
BEIYU HIGH SCHOOL

01:41.080 --> 01:43.240
Do you know how expensive
dance lessons are?

01:44.040 --> 01:45.280
You're not a kid anymore.

01:45.800 --> 01:47.720
It's time to give up
those unrealistic fantasies.

01:47.800 --> 01:48.800
I don't need you
to spend money hiring a teacher.

01:48.880 --> 01:50.200
Can I just practice on my own?

01:50.280 --> 01:51.520
Where will you be practicing?

01:52.200 --> 01:53.960
In your aunt's living room?

01:54.040 --> 01:55.640
Or are you renting a dance studio?

01:55.720 --> 01:58.160
It's expensive, even by the hour.

02:22.880 --> 02:26.240
Your Uncle Zheng's new clinic
has been losing money,

02:26.320 --> 02:28.600
and we're also struggling financially.

02:31.200 --> 02:33.040
Doesn't Zheng Kejia need money
to study art as well?

02:33.120 --> 02:34.480
If she didn't study art,

02:34.560 --> 02:36.080
she couldn't even make it to college.

02:36.160 --> 02:38.120
Does that mean I have to give up dancing?

02:47.880 --> 02:48.840
I got it.

04:06.360 --> 04:11.320
BOWL NOODLES

05:52.240 --> 05:53.720
Why are we looking
at the elementary school?

05:55.080 --> 05:56.120
Come with me.

06:02.920 --> 06:04.360
Where are we going?

06:04.960 --> 06:08.120
Did we come here to climb stairs today?

06:08.200 --> 06:09.520
Are you tired, my junior?

06:35.600 --> 06:36.800
What are we doing here?

06:36.880 --> 06:38.120
Since you can't dance anywhere else,

06:38.200 --> 06:40.360
let's make do with this spot.

06:45.960 --> 06:47.000
What?

07:18.760 --> 07:19.680
Thank you.

07:51.840 --> 07:53.640
If there's anything you're not happy with,
just let me know.

09:11.080 --> 09:12.200
3,098 DAYS

09:14.600 --> 09:18.720
DAY 36 OF OFFICIAL COHABITATION

09:24.960 --> 09:26.200
Who is it?

09:26.280 --> 09:27.480
Who is it?

09:28.040 --> 09:29.400
Shuangjiang. Shuangjiang.

09:29.480 --> 09:30.960
- Come on. Get up.
- Come on. Let's go.

09:31.040 --> 09:32.000
- Get up now.
- Sorry about this.

09:32.080 --> 09:33.640
- What are you doing?
- Listen,

09:33.720 --> 09:35.520
your mom sold you to us.

09:39.280 --> 09:40.600
Stop right there.

11:06.720 --> 11:07.920
Can't sleep?

11:14.640 --> 11:16.200
I just finished showering
and here you are.

11:16.960 --> 11:18.760
Your intention is a bit
too obvious, you know?

11:21.720 --> 11:23.440
You want to see a handsome guy
step out of the shower?

12:12.240 --> 12:13.120
Wen Yifan,

12:16.320 --> 12:18.440
what's the meaning of this?

13:34.440 --> 13:35.680
How much longer will you hold me?

13:40.720 --> 13:41.640
Wen Yifan?

14:14.880 --> 14:15.880
Wen Yifan.

14:16.800 --> 14:17.800
You…

14:35.560 --> 14:36.720
What was that about?

15:31.920 --> 15:34.080
SANG YAN: WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?

15:35.960 --> 15:37.440
Is he upset?

15:42.120 --> 15:43.600
WHAT?

16:05.520 --> 16:07.040
DID YOU TEXT THE WRONG PERSON?

16:27.520 --> 16:29.000
What's with the thumbs-up?

16:32.400 --> 16:33.720
Morning encouragement?

16:52.960 --> 16:54.120
You messaged me on WeChat yesterday.

16:54.200 --> 16:56.400
Anything you wanted to talk about?

17:10.680 --> 17:11.760
What do you mean?

17:12.560 --> 17:14.280
You want to pretend it never happened?

17:16.640 --> 17:17.839
Is it because I didn't stay

17:17.920 --> 17:20.119
to finish setting off fireworks with you?

17:20.200 --> 17:23.400
Sorry if I ruined your mood.

17:24.480 --> 17:26.560
I was just really tired yesterday.

17:29.360 --> 17:30.400
All right.

17:34.360 --> 17:37.440
It isn't a big deal for me,

17:38.360 --> 17:40.560
but I hope you'll give me
a proper explanation if you do

17:40.640 --> 17:42.880
something like this again in the future.

17:44.960 --> 17:46.600
He's so petty.

17:53.640 --> 17:54.680
I will.

18:07.240 --> 18:08.320
What's that supposed to mean?

18:13.600 --> 18:14.680
Is she not taking responsibility?

18:22.760 --> 18:23.920
Morning.

18:24.000 --> 18:24.840
Morning.

18:29.440 --> 18:31.720
What's wrong? Did you not sleep well?

18:31.800 --> 18:33.640
I've been having restless sleep
and frequent dreams.

18:33.720 --> 18:35.920
I wonder if this happens
to all pregnant women.

18:36.000 --> 18:37.360
That must be tough.

18:37.440 --> 18:38.480
You're going through a lot.

18:38.560 --> 18:40.080
How did you sleep last night?

18:40.160 --> 18:41.760
I slept okay,

18:41.840 --> 18:44.080
but I dreamed all night.

18:44.160 --> 18:46.160
What did you dream about? Tell me.

18:46.240 --> 18:48.920
Let me, a modern-day dream expert,
interpret it for you.

18:50.400 --> 18:51.920
It'll help me feel more awake.

18:57.760 --> 18:58.600
I dreamed

19:01.760 --> 19:05.400
that I suddenly
wandered into a vast forest.

19:06.280 --> 19:08.160
I walked and walked,

19:08.240 --> 19:09.800
searching for an exit,

19:09.880 --> 19:11.520
but I just couldn't.

19:19.240 --> 19:20.280
After some time,

19:20.360 --> 19:22.200
as I kept moving forward,
night fell without warning,

19:23.560 --> 19:25.400
and the cold crept in.

19:26.640 --> 19:29.000
So, I hurried forward.

19:29.760 --> 19:31.320
As I continued walking,

19:31.400 --> 19:32.960
I suddenly remembered

19:33.040 --> 19:34.920
that I had seen the sun

19:35.000 --> 19:36.120
on my way in.

19:59.960 --> 20:01.440
So, I thought

20:02.320 --> 20:04.440
maybe I should go back
and find it to warm up.

20:05.800 --> 20:06.800
After walking for a while,

20:06.880 --> 20:09.080
I really did find the sun.

20:11.720 --> 20:14.160
Didn't night already fall?
How could there still be a sun?

20:16.600 --> 20:18.160
That's why it's a dream.

20:19.880 --> 20:20.720
That's all?

20:21.600 --> 20:22.440
So, in the end…

20:22.520 --> 20:24.720
I found my way out when I saw the sun.

20:39.360 --> 20:40.880
I remember

20:42.160 --> 20:43.920
that when I saw it,

20:45.600 --> 20:47.360
I couldn't help

20:47.440 --> 20:49.400
but hug it.

21:01.840 --> 21:03.520
This dream…

21:06.440 --> 21:08.760
- Is it hard to interpret?
- Not easy.

21:13.520 --> 21:17.280
WHEN YOU ARE OLD

21:33.360 --> 21:35.080
I'LL LEND THIS TO YOU
DON'T JUST READ TEXTBOOKS

21:35.160 --> 21:36.520
READING POETRY HELPS YOU DREAM

21:42.400 --> 21:45.160
WHEN YOU'RE OLD, I'LL STILL CHERISH

21:45.240 --> 21:46.680
THE TIME WE SPENT TOGETHER

21:48.920 --> 21:51.240
By the way,
did you get the book I returned to you?

22:05.320 --> 22:08.600
WHEN YOU'RE OLD, I'LL STILL CHERISH

22:08.680 --> 22:12.000
THE TIME WE SPENT TOGETHER

22:19.000 --> 22:21.080
There's an urgent task
from the higher-ups.

22:21.160 --> 22:23.200
It's about the person from the Central
South Century City case last time.

22:23.280 --> 22:25.320
That individual is getting
a lot of attention on our channel,

22:25.400 --> 22:26.560
so the higher-ups want to strike

22:26.640 --> 22:27.760
while the iron is hot and do a follow-up.

22:27.840 --> 22:29.720
That person and Yifan
went to the same high school,

22:29.800 --> 22:30.640
- so…
- So…

22:30.720 --> 22:33.000
So, have Yifan help you get in touch.
The first draft is due tomorrow.

22:34.080 --> 22:36.000
She's already handled everything alone
during the Spring Festival.

22:36.080 --> 22:37.680
We can't have her working overtime again.

22:37.760 --> 22:39.200
All right, miss?

22:42.160 --> 22:43.760
Here's another task that isn't so urgent.
You can take care of it.

22:44.760 --> 22:45.920
Okay.

22:47.560 --> 22:48.640
Give it to me.

22:49.600 --> 22:51.600
- What?
- Your high school friend's number,

22:51.680 --> 22:52.520
so you won't feel awkward.

22:54.040 --> 22:55.400
Let me ask him for you first.

22:55.480 --> 22:56.320
Sure.

23:06.920 --> 23:08.080
Hello and welcome.

23:08.160 --> 23:09.560
- I'm here to see someone.
- This way, please.

23:09.640 --> 23:10.480
Okay.

23:14.680 --> 23:16.040
- Qiao.
- Xiang Lang.

23:18.520 --> 23:21.080
Why did you pick such a fancy restaurant?

23:21.160 --> 23:22.880
I thought you wanted a quiet place?

23:24.440 --> 23:25.320
You must be hungry.

23:25.400 --> 23:26.320
Take a look.

23:26.400 --> 23:27.760
- Okay.
- See what you'd like to eat.

23:29.280 --> 23:30.520
Any recommendations?

23:30.600 --> 23:33.160
We just added a new set menu for couples.

23:34.920 --> 23:36.160
We are not…

23:36.240 --> 23:37.880
We'll go with the set menu for couples.

23:38.560 --> 23:40.160
All right, please wait a moment.

23:44.640 --> 23:45.680
Xiang Lang.

23:46.400 --> 23:49.240
Do you remember this bracelet?

23:50.080 --> 23:51.640
Isn't this the one I gave you?

23:51.720 --> 23:52.560
You've been wearing it all this time?

23:54.080 --> 23:56.160
I've been wearing it ever since the day
you gave it to me.

23:57.800 --> 24:01.480
Even when it didn't match
my outfits, I still kept it on.

24:06.600 --> 24:08.800
- Qiao, actually…
- I've always wanted to ask you this.

24:10.440 --> 24:11.920
When you gave me this bracelet,

24:13.080 --> 24:14.960
was it just a birthday gift?

24:16.040 --> 24:18.080
I don't quite understand

24:18.600 --> 24:19.560
what you mean.

24:19.640 --> 24:20.880
I just want to know

24:22.160 --> 24:24.840
if you had even
the slightest feelings for me

24:25.520 --> 24:26.720
when you gave me

24:27.520 --> 24:29.480
this bracelet.

24:31.200 --> 24:33.320
Qiao, did I somehow
give you the wrong idea?

24:34.880 --> 24:35.720
I'm sorry.

24:35.800 --> 24:38.160
We've always just been close friends.

24:43.320 --> 24:44.520
Seems like

24:45.160 --> 24:46.720
I was reading too much into it.

24:53.320 --> 24:54.360
But…

24:56.720 --> 24:58.000
is there a chance

24:58.920 --> 25:00.640
you might see me

25:01.240 --> 25:03.280
as someone

25:04.280 --> 25:08.840
you could be with from now on?

25:15.960 --> 25:16.800
Actually, I…

25:16.880 --> 25:18.520
I guess the couple's
set menu is off the table.

25:18.600 --> 25:21.080
Let's order something else. Excuse me.

25:22.680 --> 25:23.560
I'm here.

25:24.640 --> 25:25.760
Have you been waiting for long?

25:28.280 --> 25:29.480
You haven't ordered yet?

25:30.760 --> 25:31.960
I was about to say this earlier.

25:32.800 --> 25:34.320
It's not just the two of us today,

25:36.120 --> 25:36.960
but three.

25:39.440 --> 25:40.960
What's happening?
It feels a little awkward.

25:42.320 --> 25:45.040
No, I misunderstood Xiang Lang.

25:45.920 --> 25:46.840
My bad.

25:47.360 --> 25:49.480
You actually got Qiao to apologize to you?

25:49.560 --> 25:51.200
I'm impressed.

25:53.240 --> 25:54.080
Let's order first.

25:54.160 --> 25:55.920
You two eat.
I have to take care of something.

25:56.000 --> 25:57.040
Qiao.

25:58.160 --> 25:59.520
What exactly is happening here?

26:00.800 --> 26:02.160
It's all my fault.

26:04.680 --> 26:05.880
Let me explain to both of you.

26:08.560 --> 26:10.160
That bracelet

26:11.440 --> 26:13.360
was actually something I wanted you

26:13.440 --> 26:14.960
to pass on to Dian back then.

26:17.480 --> 26:18.320
Qiao.

26:19.040 --> 26:19.920
Xiang Lang.

26:20.640 --> 26:23.000
Sorry for the last-minute meetup.

26:23.080 --> 26:24.040
No worries.

26:24.120 --> 26:26.080
It's not often that you ask me to meet up.

26:30.360 --> 26:32.120
I couldn't change my parents' minds.

26:32.200 --> 26:34.120
They've already booked me
a flight to the U.S. for tomorrow,

26:35.480 --> 26:36.320
so…

26:37.120 --> 26:38.200
I want to…

26:39.360 --> 26:42.080
I thought you and Dian
had forgotten my birthday.

26:42.160 --> 26:43.920
Thank you.

26:46.040 --> 26:48.640
That's right. It's your birthday today.
Happy birthday!

26:48.720 --> 26:50.000
Thank you.

26:50.080 --> 26:51.720
This bracelet is gorgeous.

26:51.800 --> 26:52.640
It must have cost a lot, didn't it?

26:53.880 --> 26:54.800
Not really.

26:55.480 --> 26:58.280
So, you said your parents
booked you a flight.

26:58.360 --> 26:59.600
What's it for? A vacation?

27:01.240 --> 27:03.800
I'm leaving for the U.S. to study.

27:08.160 --> 27:10.840
I should have been upfront with you.

27:11.920 --> 27:13.040
I also

27:13.600 --> 27:15.400
should have confessed my feelings earlier.

27:16.560 --> 27:17.720
This is all on me.

27:21.280 --> 27:22.400
Dian.

27:25.000 --> 27:26.680
I've actually

27:27.400 --> 27:29.160
felt differently about you

27:29.720 --> 27:30.560
since high school.

27:31.800 --> 27:32.640
What are you talking about?

27:40.640 --> 27:41.480
It's me who should apologize.

27:42.440 --> 27:43.960
I've been deluded,

27:44.480 --> 27:45.600
holding onto something

27:45.680 --> 27:47.040
that wasn't mine for all these years.

27:48.400 --> 27:50.200
You two eat. I still have work to do.

27:50.280 --> 27:51.480
- Qiao.
- Qiao.

27:57.760 --> 27:59.080
Dian, I…

28:18.560 --> 28:19.840
Ms. Qian…

28:25.960 --> 28:27.600
All right. I'm heading over now.

28:27.680 --> 28:29.520
Dian, where are you going?

28:29.600 --> 28:31.320
I'm going to the TV station.

28:32.760 --> 28:34.960
Get in the car. I'll give you a ride.
We can have a chat on the way.

29:01.080 --> 29:01.920
No need to keep wondering.

29:03.080 --> 29:04.000
She's just not into you.

29:10.720 --> 29:11.920
Tell me.

29:12.000 --> 29:13.760
What kind of flirtatious moves
did she make?

29:15.280 --> 29:16.520
She hugged you?

29:27.800 --> 29:29.840
Since you're both girls,
I'd like you to answer this for me.

29:34.800 --> 29:36.480
This person hugged my friend

29:38.400 --> 29:40.560
and acted like
nothing happened the next day.

29:41.360 --> 29:42.280
What do you think that means?

29:45.080 --> 29:46.320
Shouldn't this kind
of irresponsible behavior

29:46.400 --> 29:48.040
be reported to the police?

29:54.680 --> 29:56.960
It shouldn't be so serious
if it was just a hug, right?

30:03.400 --> 30:05.920
Are you out of your mind?
Why report it to the police?

30:11.640 --> 30:13.320
But really,

30:14.480 --> 30:16.520
it depends on the nature
of your friend's relationship

30:16.600 --> 30:17.880
with this girl.

30:19.080 --> 30:21.840
Maybe the girl was feeling down

30:21.920 --> 30:23.200
and just needed some comfort,

30:23.840 --> 30:27.000
so the hug might not mean much.

30:27.520 --> 30:29.240
It could simply be a hug between friends.

30:34.840 --> 30:36.200
I'm just speculating, though.

30:36.280 --> 30:38.000
I don't know their relationship,

30:39.200 --> 30:42.320
so my opinion might not be very helpful.

30:43.360 --> 30:44.560
Here's the question.

30:44.640 --> 30:46.080
How's your relationship?

30:46.160 --> 30:47.680
How else could the relationship be?

30:47.760 --> 30:48.840
She's my goddess.

30:48.920 --> 30:49.960
I've been pursuing her
for over half a year.

30:50.040 --> 30:51.720
And what are you even talking about?

30:51.800 --> 30:53.120
Didn't I explain everything already?

30:53.200 --> 30:56.080
She gave me a box of chocolates
on Valentine's Day,

30:56.160 --> 30:57.160
not a hug.

30:57.920 --> 30:59.000
The real issue is

30:59.080 --> 31:00.520
that after giving me the chocolates,

31:00.600 --> 31:02.280
she never contacted me again.

31:02.360 --> 31:04.760
She's someone
who is madly in love with him.

31:10.880 --> 31:13.320
Your friend must have quite the charisma.

31:17.560 --> 31:20.160
Did this girl confess to him?

31:21.800 --> 31:22.920
Why do you ask?

31:23.800 --> 31:26.040
It just doesn't make sense logically.

31:27.120 --> 31:29.280
If this girl really likes your friend,

31:29.360 --> 31:31.520
then the meaning of the hug
should be pretty clear.

31:36.160 --> 31:38.720
But your friend probably doesn't need
to bring this up with you.

31:38.800 --> 31:40.960
So, are you implying

31:41.480 --> 31:42.840
that love has clouded his judgment?

31:42.920 --> 31:45.320
From what I just heard
you say to your friend,

31:45.400 --> 31:47.400
it seems like this girl
hasn't clearly expressed

31:47.480 --> 31:48.440
her feelings.

31:52.040 --> 31:53.760
So, is it possible
that your friend misunderstood?

31:53.840 --> 31:56.160
Misunderstood? What did he misunderstand?

31:58.240 --> 31:59.560
Simply put,

32:00.080 --> 32:01.280
it's just him

32:02.400 --> 32:03.560
imagining things.

32:13.920 --> 32:15.160
Did you hear that?

32:15.240 --> 32:16.880
It's just you imagining things.

32:16.960 --> 32:18.840
- Now, leave me alone.
- Wait, Sang Yan. What's wrong with--?

32:33.960 --> 32:35.480
Are you done yet?

32:35.560 --> 32:36.840
What's your problem?

32:39.560 --> 32:40.440
It's you.

32:41.200 --> 32:42.560
I thought it was Chen Junwen.

32:43.080 --> 32:43.960
What's the matter?

32:44.040 --> 32:45.880
Su Haoan mentioned in the group chat

32:45.960 --> 32:46.880
that you went to Yihe recently.

32:47.640 --> 32:48.600
Were you there for me?

32:48.680 --> 32:49.880
What group chat? How come I didn't see it?

32:49.960 --> 32:51.080
You're not in this group chat.

32:51.160 --> 32:53.040
Seriously?

32:53.120 --> 32:54.080
Is this necessary?

32:54.600 --> 32:55.600
Stop changing the subject.

32:56.200 --> 32:57.360
Be honest with me.

32:57.440 --> 32:59.240
Have you been to Yihe more than once?

33:00.280 --> 33:01.400
What were you doing there?

33:41.280 --> 33:43.600
You've never loved me, have you?

33:44.200 --> 33:45.960
You've been toying with me, haven't you?

33:47.320 --> 33:48.760
Say something!

33:49.880 --> 33:50.960
Why?

33:51.040 --> 33:53.000
Why do you always dress like…?

34:09.320 --> 34:10.840
Sir, I've already bought
everything you need

34:10.920 --> 34:12.159
for your stay in the hospital.

34:12.239 --> 34:14.360
If there's anything else you need,
just let me know.

34:14.440 --> 34:16.719
- Thank you.
- The nurse will take you upstairs.

34:17.719 --> 34:18.639
Take care.

34:19.920 --> 34:21.360
Let's go, sir.

34:21.440 --> 34:22.480
Bye.

34:22.560 --> 34:26.120
NANWU WEST DISTRICT HOSPITAL

34:54.040 --> 34:55.880
I really don't blame you for this.

34:55.960 --> 34:58.800
I can't blame anyone for things like this.

34:58.880 --> 35:00.800
I probably just need some time.

35:03.840 --> 35:05.800
I don't think you truly understand me.

35:06.320 --> 35:07.400
I tend to avoid things,

35:08.160 --> 35:09.360
and I'm not very outgoing.

35:10.040 --> 35:11.440
To protect myself,

35:13.440 --> 35:15.920
I could leave everything behind
without hesitation.

35:17.800 --> 35:19.240
The person you imagine me to be

35:20.480 --> 35:22.640
is probably not the same
as the one I'm describing.

35:27.600 --> 35:28.520
You really deserve someone better.

35:36.400 --> 35:38.600
I've made things clear with Xiang Lang.

35:38.680 --> 35:40.560
I don't want any misunderstandings
between the three of us.

35:40.640 --> 35:43.000
Is it because of me that you…?

35:43.080 --> 35:45.240
If I really got together with Xiang Lang,
would you cut ties with me?

35:45.320 --> 35:47.680
Of course not. It's a different time now.

35:47.760 --> 35:50.480
Who would ditch
their best friend for a man?

35:55.560 --> 35:58.160
Actually, the main reason
I rejected Xiang Lang

35:58.240 --> 36:00.160
is that I don't have
any romantic feelings for him.

36:02.920 --> 36:05.240
Just like how he feels about me.

36:06.000 --> 36:07.320
But Xiang Lang

36:08.000 --> 36:10.080
is still a very good friend
to us, isn't he?

36:21.040 --> 36:22.680
I don't want to grow up at all.

36:22.760 --> 36:25.160
Growing up just makes
everything so complicated.

36:25.240 --> 36:27.160
Wouldn't it be better
to be as simple as before?

36:30.600 --> 36:32.160
It's love that makes things complicated.

36:35.320 --> 36:39.440
It's inherently an emotion
of extreme love and hate.

36:47.120 --> 36:50.760
Let's sweep away all the negativity.

36:52.960 --> 36:55.080
Knock them all down
with one throw. Come on.

37:01.720 --> 37:02.920
You just can't let go, can you?

37:03.000 --> 37:04.240
Watch me instead.

37:09.400 --> 37:10.720
The one in front of you right now

37:10.800 --> 37:12.600
is from our Lily of the Valley collection.

37:12.680 --> 37:14.240
"Happiness Returns
as the Lily of the Valley Blooms",

37:14.320 --> 37:17.280
which also symbolizes a life
filled with happiness and fulfillment.

37:17.800 --> 37:18.720
This one looks great.

37:19.880 --> 37:21.160
The other one was too expensive,

37:21.240 --> 37:22.880
and it was inconvenient
to wear while working.

37:22.960 --> 37:24.400
This one suits me better.

37:24.480 --> 37:26.480
It looks great indeed.

37:26.560 --> 37:27.440
It's a brilliant choice.

37:29.000 --> 37:30.320
We should both be kinder to ourselves.

37:31.960 --> 37:34.520
So, are we officially best friends now?

37:34.600 --> 37:36.880
No more annoying guys getting in the way.

37:36.960 --> 37:37.920
Sure.

37:38.000 --> 37:40.200
From now on, there will be no men,
only best friends.

38:00.000 --> 38:00.960
Thanks.

38:05.160 --> 38:06.080
Here.

38:06.160 --> 38:08.160
It's a good day to get a bit tipsy.

38:08.880 --> 38:10.160
This new lychee flavor

38:10.240 --> 38:13.680
is perfect for reminiscing
about summer romances.

38:13.760 --> 38:14.800
Try it.

38:23.000 --> 38:24.840
There's something I've been
curious about for a while,

38:24.920 --> 38:26.120
but I never asked you.

38:27.400 --> 38:28.400
Have you never had

38:28.480 --> 38:29.720
any feelings for Sang Yan before?

38:33.680 --> 38:34.600
Why are you suddenly asking this?

38:34.680 --> 38:36.160
Because he's handsome,

38:36.240 --> 38:38.280
and he's really quite charming.

38:38.800 --> 38:40.880
Even though I barely
talked to him in high school,

38:40.960 --> 38:43.440
I knew that he seemed to really like you

38:44.040 --> 38:45.600
and treated you well.

38:50.680 --> 38:51.920
If you don't say anything,
I'll just assume

38:52.000 --> 38:53.240
you did have feelings for him.

38:56.120 --> 38:57.000
Okay.

38:59.640 --> 39:01.760
So, I can take this as you admit it?

39:03.440 --> 39:05.080
For real?

39:06.200 --> 39:07.080
What's with this reaction?

39:07.680 --> 39:09.520
So, you really had feelings
for Sang Yan back then?

39:10.640 --> 39:12.200
What about now?
Do you still feel the same?

39:12.880 --> 39:14.040
That was long in the past.

39:14.120 --> 39:16.960
But you are roommates now,
spending so much time around each other.

39:17.040 --> 39:19.840
Besides, you both had feelings
for each other before.

39:19.920 --> 39:21.840
What if those feelings resurface?

39:24.200 --> 39:26.360
That won't happen. He's moving out soon.

39:29.720 --> 39:31.240
So, you're implying

39:31.320 --> 39:32.760
that if he stayed longer,

39:33.520 --> 39:35.000
you might have given in to your feelings.

39:39.880 --> 39:42.400
But why didn't you two
get together before?

39:43.880 --> 39:44.720
Oh, I get it now.

39:44.800 --> 39:46.360
It was because you transferred schools
and moved away,

39:46.440 --> 39:48.440
so you lost contact.

39:52.320 --> 39:55.360
- No.
- Why then?

40:01.680 --> 40:03.760
I don't know if others

40:03.840 --> 40:06.320
would behave the way I do. But…

40:09.000 --> 40:10.320
But my college roommate once told me

40:11.240 --> 40:12.840
that she thought

40:12.920 --> 40:13.920
I was emotionally distant.

40:14.880 --> 40:16.360
We were close,

40:17.000 --> 40:19.200
but once we graduated,
it felt like we lost touch.

40:19.880 --> 40:22.080
I hardly ever reached out to them,

40:23.560 --> 40:25.560
and they were pretty upset about it.

40:30.520 --> 40:31.680
I admit that.

40:32.360 --> 40:33.520
Take Xiang Lang, for example.

40:33.600 --> 40:35.440
After he went abroad,
we barely kept in touch.

40:37.800 --> 40:38.960
I think

40:39.480 --> 40:41.640
it's a natural thing

40:42.480 --> 40:43.640
for people to drift apart

40:45.880 --> 40:47.480
over time.

40:51.640 --> 40:54.800
And back then, I just thought

40:55.640 --> 40:57.160
someone like Sang Yan

41:00.440 --> 41:02.400
deserved

41:04.720 --> 41:06.480
to be loved passionately.

41:39.480 --> 41:46.000
THE STORY IS NOT OVER YET…

41:54.320 --> 41:57.200
Why does she look so unhappy?

42:07.560 --> 42:14.280
TO WEN YIFAN
SANG YAN: WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?

42:44.720 --> 42:45.920
Can't sleep?

42:47.680 --> 42:49.440
You want to see a handsome guy
step out of the shower?

45:47.360 --> 45:48.600
HUGE THANKS TO EVERYONE INVOLVED
AND TO ALL THE FANS OF THE FIRST FROST!

45:48.680 --> 45:49.640
TREAT YOURSELF WELL
AND THE WORLD WILL HOLD MORE LOVE FOR YOU!
